The paper proposes an approach for learning probabilistic machine learning models within the context of stochastic programming, which involves optimization and decision-making under uncertainty. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Given that the paper focuses on end-to-end learning of models that directly capture the ultimate task-based objective, it is most likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more focused on specific aspects of the problem (e.g., decision-making, control, data structures).
